29:46.262 --> 29:48.525
I have this news feed alarm
for American news.

29:48.569 --> 29:51.180
Whenever I hear that ding,
I know that it's bad.

29:51.224 --> 29:52.921
Well, maybe it'll be good
this time.

29:56.011 --> 29:57.186
No.

29:58.187 --> 30:00.059
So, the oral arguments are done

30:00.102 --> 30:01.582
over teleconferencing
these days.

30:01.625 --> 30:03.497
You'll talk into
this camera here.

30:03.540 --> 30:04.890
-That one?
-Yes.

30:04.933 --> 30:06.587
And there are home Zoom screens

30:06.630 --> 30:09.068
of the Supreme Court justices
on these three screens.

30:09.111 --> 30:10.896
And the Chief Justice is

30:10.939 --> 30:11.897
-on this screen.
-Okay.

30:11.940 --> 30:13.507
-And they can see me?
-Yes.

30:13.550 --> 30:15.030
-Do you want to see yourself?
-No.

30:15.074 --> 30:16.075
Okay.

30:16.118 --> 30:18.251
-Who's this?
-Oh. My husband.

30:18.294 --> 30:20.079
-Hi. Leopold.
-Kurt.

30:20.122 --> 30:21.471
No! Don't shake hands.

30:22.516 --> 30:24.257
I'm sorry about this, Kurt.

30:24.300 --> 30:26.128
We're setting up
for oral arguments.

30:26.172 --> 30:28.478
Do you want the guns
in the background?

30:29.523 --> 30:31.003
Yes.

30:31.046 --> 30:33.657
They think that makes me seem
like less of a nut.

30:33.701 --> 30:35.050
-Maybe you should have a...

30:35.094 --> 30:36.704
...ammunition belt
over your shoulder.

30:36.747 --> 30:38.532
Thank you, Kurt.

30:38.575 --> 30:39.925
Hey, Diane.

30:39.968 --> 30:42.492
-Hmm?
-Sir, please. Can you step away?

30:43.537 --> 30:45.147
I need a minute with my wife.

30:47.149 --> 30:49.151
Yeah, can you grab that light,
move it over there?

30:49.195 --> 30:50.283
Close the door.

30:52.372 --> 30:54.113
What?

31:07.213 --> 31:08.388
Oh, no.

31:08.431 --> 31:11.217
-I'll send them away.
-Oh, no.

31:11.260 --> 31:14.394
-2020 just won't let go.

31:14.437 --> 31:16.135
I'm so sorry.

31:17.527 --> 31:19.312
Oh, no.

31:21.444 --> 31:23.142
It's over.

31:23.185 --> 31:25.622
He gets to nominate someone.

31:25.666 --> 31:27.537
Another Kavanaugh.

31:27.581 --> 31:30.758
We'll have a conservative court
for the next 20 years--

31:30.801 --> 31:33.326
-my whole fucking life!

31:33.369 --> 31:35.328
We're all set.

31:35.371 --> 31:37.765
They don't want
an oral argument now,

31:37.808 --> 31:39.549
-not with RBG gone.

31:39.593 --> 31:40.550
Ms. Lockhart.
-Give us a minute.

31:40.594 --> 31:42.770
Oh, babe.

31:42.813 --> 31:44.337
I don't deserve you.

31:44.380 --> 31:46.121
Oh, stop.

31:46.165 --> 31:48.994
You don't agree with me.

31:49.037 --> 31:51.735
I can still feel bad for you.

31:56.044 --> 31:57.785
What do we do?

31:57.828 --> 31:59.526
They're killing us.

31:59.569 --> 32:01.354
Who are they killing?

32:01.397 --> 32:04.400
Black men, women, the young.

32:04.444 --> 32:06.359
What do we do?

32:06.402 --> 32:10.363
Talk. Understand. Unite.

32:10.406 --> 32:12.234
Even with white supremacists?

32:12.278 --> 32:14.193
I would unite with anybody
to do right,

32:14.236 --> 32:15.455
with nobody to do wrong.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.065
Mm, no.
Why am I talking to you?

32:17.109 --> 32:18.371
You're just
a <i>Soul Train</i> commercial.

32:18.414 --> 32:20.590
What about me?

32:22.331 --> 32:23.767
Karl Marx?

32:23.811 --> 32:25.378
I'm guessing you're
from a college extension course

32:25.421 --> 32:26.509
I took on economics.

32:26.553 --> 32:27.771
Why don't people think

32:27.815 --> 32:29.425
I am about more
than economics, huh?

32:29.469 --> 32:32.515
-I have a life, too.
-But you can't tell me nothing

32:32.559 --> 32:34.169
about Black people
being killed now.

32:34.213 --> 32:35.475
And what about me?

32:35.518 --> 32:37.390
You're from my mother.

32:37.433 --> 32:38.782
That's why you're here.

32:38.826 --> 32:40.262
So, you don't believe in me?

32:41.307 --> 32:43.787
I guess I do
because you're here.

32:43.831 --> 32:45.311
-Can I say something?
-Yeah.

32:45.354 --> 32:47.400
-You're Jesus. Go ahead.
-I'm a historical figure,

32:47.443 --> 32:49.402
like Napoleon or Cicero.

32:49.445 --> 32:51.230
So I don't understand
why people have to talk

32:51.273 --> 32:52.753
about believing in me.

32:52.796 --> 32:54.581
Because you're an opium
for the masses.

32:54.624 --> 32:56.148
See, that is such nonsense.
I am the salvation...

32:58.237 --> 33:00.674
Wait. Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Let me ask you...

33:01.718 --> 33:04.286
What do I do about George Floyd?

33:08.551 --> 33:11.119
Whoa, hold up, hold up,
hold up. Please, please.

33:11.163 --> 33:12.860
Please, please, please, please.

33:12.903 --> 33:15.254
When else can I get you three
together?

33:15.297 --> 33:16.516
Four.

33:17.560 --> 33:19.780
Okay, good.

33:19.823 --> 33:21.260
That fills a poker table.

33:21.303 --> 33:22.609
The four of you.

33:22.652 --> 33:25.177
What do I do about George Floyd?

33:25.220 --> 33:27.266
-Wait, wait!

33:27.309 --> 33:29.616
Wait, you all are talking
at the same time.

33:29.659 --> 33:32.619
Jay is right.
Let's start chronologically.

33:32.662 --> 33:34.621
-Jesus Christ.
-Thank you.

33:34.664 --> 33:37.711
The key is to avoid
the violence.

33:37.754 --> 33:40.583
Violence poisons
the perpetrator,

33:40.627 --> 33:42.629
but it also poisons the cause.

33:43.978 --> 33:48.591
-Karl.
-This is all about the upper
class versus the lower.

33:48.635 --> 33:52.856
Race is just an avatar
for issues of class.

33:52.900 --> 33:54.467
-Malcolm?
-It is criminal

33:54.510 --> 33:56.338
to teach a man
not to defend himself

33:56.382 --> 33:58.601
when he is the constant victim
of brutal attacks.

33:58.645 --> 34:00.168
And these are brutal attacks.

34:00.212 --> 34:01.691
-Brutal attacks? Brutal attacks?
Now, wait a minute.

34:01.735 --> 34:03.476
So you would have Jay lash out?

34:03.519 --> 34:05.043
No.

34:05.086 --> 34:07.610
But until the oppressors
are ready to follow you, Jesus,

34:07.654 --> 34:09.743
or even you, Mr. Douglass,

34:09.786 --> 34:10.787
Jay...

34:11.875 --> 34:14.661
...you need to fight
the oppressor.

34:20.362 --> 34:21.842
This is your test.

34:29.589 --> 34:30.720
<i>So, we're looking at Arizona,</i>

34:30.764 --> 34:32.679
<i>more to the West Coast,
obviously,</i>

34:32.722 --> 34:36.422
<i>where you can see Joe Biden is
right now 34,035 votes ahead.</i>

34:36.465 --> 34:38.380
<i>can Biden hold on to this lead?</i>

34:38.424 --> 34:39.555
Kurt, you don't
have to stay here.

34:39.599 --> 34:40.904
Watch Fox in the other room.

34:40.948 --> 34:43.864
I'm fine.
I think you need it more.

34:43.907 --> 34:45.518
<i>It would be the first time
this red state</i>

34:45.561 --> 34:47.520
<i>has turned blue since 1996.</i>

34:47.563 --> 34:49.391
Yes, but,
Kurt, if you stay,

34:49.435 --> 34:51.872
I know this isn't sensible,
but...

34:51.915 --> 34:53.308
Trump seems to get more votes

34:53.352 --> 34:54.744
whenever you're sitting
on this couch.

34:54.788 --> 34:56.442
Are you serious?

34:56.485 --> 34:59.358
I am so deathly serious.

34:59.401 --> 35:02.491
Whenever you're sitting here,
Arizona goes for Trump.

35:03.579 --> 35:06.452
Humor me, please.
Just go in the other room.

35:07.496 --> 35:09.237
No, no, no. No kiss.

35:09.281 --> 35:11.587
If you kiss me,
we'll lose Georgia.

35:11.631 --> 35:14.373
Uh, if you lose,
we'll be fine, right?

35:14.416 --> 35:15.722
Kurt, let me just say this.

35:15.765 --> 35:18.855
I'm only saying
that we won't be fine

35:18.899 --> 35:21.380
so that the universe
will grant me a win.

35:21.423 --> 35:22.990
Understood.

35:23.033 --> 35:25.993
<i>Phoenix voted for a Republican
candidate every election</i>

35:26.036 --> 35:27.821
<i>since 1952.</i>

35:27.864 --> 35:29.605
<i>That means you have to go back
to Harry Truman</i>

35:29.649 --> 35:31.607
<i>to find the last time
it went blue.</i>

35:31.651 --> 35:34.654
<i>-Will 2020 be the year
that Maricopa changes?</i>

35:34.697 --> 35:37.309
<i>Will it be enough for Biden
to win it all, or...</i>

35:37.352 --> 35:39.485
-Here.
-That's the...

35:39.528 --> 35:41.226
that's the champagne
from the back of the fridge?

35:41.269 --> 35:43.619
-Yeah.
-That was for when Hillary won.

35:43.663 --> 35:46.231
I-I can only drink it
if Biden wins.

35:46.274 --> 35:49.321
It's odd you progressives
resisted religion.

35:49.364 --> 35:51.975
You seem to have a hundred
religions to take its place.

35:52.019 --> 35:54.413
Go away, Trump.
I mean, Kurt.

35:54.456 --> 35:55.718
I'm going.

35:55.762 --> 35:58.417
Uh, love me even if,
uh, you lose.

35:58.460 --> 35:59.983
<i>...it's called Maricopa County,</i>

36:00.027 --> 36:02.943
<i>located in the South Central
part of the state.</i>

36:02.986 --> 36:05.032
-I'll think about it! <i>
-Moving over to
Pennsylvania now.</i>

36:05.075 --> 36:08.427
<i>Right now, Trump is up
by about 130,000 votes,</i>

36:08.470 --> 36:10.951
<i>but the most Democratic counties
are still out.</i>

36:10.994 --> 36:13.519
<i>does Biden have enough votes</i>

36:13.562 --> 36:14.824
<i>to make up the difference?</i>

36:14.868 --> 36:16.304
<i>As the night wears on,</i>

36:16.348 --> 36:17.958
<i>we see that Diane has found
more pockets</i>

36:18.001 --> 36:20.395
<i>of blue blood cells
in Pennsylvania,</i>

36:20.439 --> 36:22.832
<i>and fewer red blood cells
in these regions.</i>

36:22.876 --> 36:24.573
<i>You'll see here,</i>

36:24.617 --> 36:27.272
<i>right around the red blood clot
blocking the coronary artery.</i>

36:27.315 --> 36:28.751
<i>That is what local officials</i>

36:28.795 --> 36:30.971
call the myocardial infarction.

36:31.014 --> 36:33.800
And as you see here,
bringing it up again,

36:33.843 --> 36:35.628
<i>I bring up
the right heart valve.</i>

36:35.671 --> 36:38.457
<i>The coronary arteries bring
blood and oxygen to the heart.</i>

36:38.500 --> 36:40.459
-Oh, my God. <i>
-If the blood flow is blocked,</i>

36:40.502 --> 36:42.635
the heart is starved of oxygen
and heart cells die.

36:42.678 --> 36:45.290
So Biden needs to win
the commonwealth

36:45.333 --> 36:46.726
of the right ventricle,

36:46.769 --> 36:49.772
<i>or Diane will have
a coronary event of some kind.</i>

36:49.816 --> 36:51.426
Okay, God.

36:51.470 --> 36:53.646
<i>If the blue blood cells
of the inferior vein...</i>

36:53.689 --> 36:55.561
You know I don't believe in you,

36:55.604 --> 36:57.650
but I will believe in you
if Joe Biden wins.

36:57.693 --> 37:00.087
<i>...then the district of Lockhart
will avoid a myocardial...</i>

37:00.130 --> 37:02.829
I'm sorry. I know that
that's not what Jesus taught.

37:02.872 --> 37:04.831
There's nothing in
the New Testament that says,

37:04.874 --> 37:07.442
"Believe in me, and I'll
make sure your candidate wins,"

37:07.486 --> 37:09.531
but I need Joe Biden to win.

37:09.575 --> 37:13.492
I'm sorry, God, but I just do.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.015
<i>...locked in a basement
in Delaware...</i>

37:15.058 --> 37:16.930
I need some faith.

37:17.974 --> 37:20.020
Anything?

37:20.063 --> 37:21.587
Military votes in Arizona.

37:21.630 --> 37:23.893
Georgia thinks they'll be done
counting votes tonight.

37:23.937 --> 37:25.504
Oh, I thought you were
checking in on Jay.

37:25.547 --> 37:26.853
Oh, no, sorry.

37:26.896 --> 37:27.854
He was texting me.

37:27.897 --> 37:28.942
I think he's getting out today.

37:29.986 --> 37:31.858
All rise.

37:31.901 --> 37:34.556
The Honorable Judge
Trig Mullaney presiding.

37:34.600 --> 37:37.864
It is like I am being smothered
in these things. You can sit.

37:38.908 --> 37:40.606
Do we have a new president yet?

37:40.649 --> 37:42.738
-Not as yet, Your Honor.
-Well,

37:42.782 --> 37:45.045
whatever they say about Trump,
he was good for the courts.

37:45.088 --> 37:47.700
Anyway, I've made my decision
on this case--

37:47.743 --> 37:49.615
the, uh... the bribery one.

37:49.658 --> 37:53.096
Oh. Do you want us to stand,
Your Honor?

37:54.402 --> 37:57.057
I thought you were.
Yes, I do.

37:59.102 --> 38:02.715
So, bribery is a bad thing,

38:02.758 --> 38:05.718
and the state can't condone it.
Neither can I.

38:05.761 --> 38:07.415
"Nee-ther," "ni-ther."

38:07.459 --> 38:08.416
"Nee-ther" can...

38:08.460 --> 38:09.635
"Ni-ther" can I?

38:09.678 --> 38:12.028
"Ni-ther" sounds better, right?
"Ni-ther."

38:12.072 --> 38:13.552
-Neither can I.
-I have a sick feeling.

38:13.595 --> 38:15.423
-Either way we appeal.
-So, that...

38:15.467 --> 38:16.859
is why I find you guilty

38:16.903 --> 38:18.905
and sentence you
to seven years in prison.

38:18.948 --> 38:20.863
We plan to appeal, Your Honor.

38:20.907 --> 38:22.778
Yep. Yep. Go for it.

38:22.822 --> 38:25.564
Anyway, that's it, I guess.

38:25.607 --> 38:27.174
Thank you. Have a nice day.

38:27.217 --> 38:28.784
-Oh-oh, my God. Seven years?
-Don't worry.

38:28.828 --> 38:30.569
-Julius...
-Seven years?

38:30.612 --> 38:32.092
-We're going to appeal.
Don't-don't worry.
-Seven years?

38:32.135 --> 38:33.746
-Tell my wife.
-I will. I will.

38:33.789 --> 38:34.921
-But, Julius, don't worry.

38:34.964 --> 38:36.009
Why not?

38:36.052 --> 38:37.097
<i>It is official.</i>

38:37.140 --> 38:39.534
By a 306 to 232 margin,

38:39.578 --> 38:43.059
<i>the Electoral College has made
Joe Biden president-elect.</i>

38:43.103 --> 38:46.019
<i>Vice President Mike Pence will
preside over the certification</i>

38:46.062 --> 38:48.195
<i>according to the Electoral
Count Act of 1877...</i>

38:48.238 --> 38:50.110
You opening it now?

38:50.153 --> 38:52.678
<i>Now many eyes will look to
the date of January 6,</i>

38:52.721 --> 38:55.594
<i>when a joint session of Congress
counts the electoral votes.</i>

38:55.637 --> 38:58.161
<i>-Many expect
a contentious debate.
-Nope.</i>

38:58.205 --> 39:01.861
If I open it now,
something bad will happen.

39:01.904 --> 39:04.124
I've waited four years.

39:04.167 --> 39:05.778
I can wait another few weeks.

39:05.821 --> 39:07.083
<i>The former vice president will
take the oath of...</i>

39:07.127 --> 39:09.042
Lucca,

39:09.085 --> 39:11.087
this firm doesn't want
to lose you.

39:11.131 --> 39:13.655
This is the best
and final offer.

39:13.699 --> 39:16.615
We can't afford to get into
a bidding war with Bianca,

39:16.658 --> 39:18.747
so we're going to need
a yes or no answer from you

39:18.791 --> 39:20.445
by the end of this call.

39:20.488 --> 39:22.185
Okay.

39:22.229 --> 39:23.970
I'm ready.

39:24.013 --> 39:25.667
With Adrian leaving,

39:25.711 --> 39:28.148
we have one spot open
for an equity partner.

39:28.191 --> 39:29.976
We will give it to you.

39:30.019 --> 39:33.066
You will be the youngest
equity partner

39:33.109 --> 39:34.676
in the history of this firm.

39:34.720 --> 39:36.809
And the firm will match
Bianca's offer

39:36.852 --> 39:38.724
of $500,000 a year.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.639
Great.

39:40.682 --> 39:41.770
But again,

39:41.814 --> 39:43.206
we can't have a bidding war.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.078
It's yes or no now.

39:46.122 --> 39:47.646
Lucca, look.

39:47.689 --> 39:49.125
History is being made
right here,

39:49.169 --> 39:50.736
right now in America.

39:50.779 --> 39:52.868
Now, you need to be part of
that, part of that tradition.

39:52.912 --> 39:55.001
England is not yours.

39:55.044 --> 39:56.785
America is.

39:56.829 --> 39:59.658
We are a Black firm, Lucca,

39:59.701 --> 40:01.877
and we need you.

40:01.921 --> 40:03.270
I don't... Wi-Fi is...

40:03.313 --> 40:04.880
<i>-Hello? Hey, guys...?
Lucca?</i>

40:04.924 --> 40:07.579
<i>-Can you... Hello?
-Can you call us back, Lucca?</i>

40:07.622 --> 40:10.233
<i>-Hello? Prob...
-Lucca, if you--
Just call us back.</i>

40:10.277 --> 40:13.149
You think she did that
on purpose?

40:13.193 --> 40:14.499
I would have.

40:14.542 --> 40:16.936
She's probably on with Bianca
right now.

40:16.979 --> 40:19.721
They used George Floyd
because they want you for less.

40:19.765 --> 40:22.071
They have never appreciated you
as much as I do.

40:22.115 --> 40:23.899
<i>All those scars,</i>

40:23.943 --> 40:26.815
<i>all that times being taken
for granted and undervalued</i>

40:26.859 --> 40:28.034
<i>has made you a fighter.</i>

40:28.077 --> 40:30.558
<i>It's made you someone
I now want.</i>

40:30.602 --> 40:31.994
<i>Do you have
your legal pad ready?</i>

40:32.038 --> 40:33.213
Yes.

40:33.256 --> 40:35.868
<i>I don't like bidding,
so here it is.</i>

40:35.911 --> 40:37.870
I want you, Lucca.

40:37.913 --> 40:39.959
$1.3 million.

40:40.002 --> 40:42.657
<i>You are my new CFO.</i>

40:44.964 --> 40:46.705
Go ahead, call them back.

40:46.748 --> 40:49.229
My guess is
they won't be able to beat that.

40:49.272 --> 40:52.711
<i>So it wasn't just
a ton of money, it was CFO.</i>

40:52.754 --> 40:55.757
<i>-And a ton of money.
So this is goodbye?</i>

40:55.801 --> 40:57.629
-I can't believe it. <i>
-It's not goodbye.</i>

40:57.672 --> 40:58.891
<i>I'll be seeing you.</i>

40:58.934 --> 41:00.980
Yeah, but like this,
on a screen.

41:01.023 --> 41:02.938
<i>Marissa, we don't have to work
together to be friends.</i>

41:02.982 --> 41:06.942
<i>-And you're gonna be
a lawyer anyway.
-What?</i>

41:06.986 --> 41:08.683
I've been going to law school.

41:08.727 --> 41:09.945
You're kidding?

41:09.989 --> 41:11.817
Y-- You didn't tell me.

41:11.860 --> 41:14.733
She's been using her time.
You should have, too.

41:14.776 --> 41:16.256
<i>How are you, Jay?</i>

41:16.299 --> 41:17.953
Getting better.

41:17.997 --> 41:21.130
I... lost my taste buds.

41:21.174 --> 41:23.089
<i>It was weird.</i>

41:23.132 --> 41:25.265
And I carry a gun now.

41:25.308 --> 41:26.396
What?

41:27.789 --> 41:28.921
It's performative.

41:29.965 --> 41:32.794
Stay safe, Jay, okay?

41:32.838 --> 41:36.102
-What are we talking about?
COVID or the protests?
-Both.

41:36.145 --> 41:38.234
Give me a ride
on your private jet, Lucca.

41:38.278 --> 41:39.975
When I get one, I will, yes.

41:40.019 --> 41:42.108
<i>I have a-a confession to make.</i>

41:42.151 --> 41:43.109
Sure.

41:43.152 --> 41:45.111
I stole...

41:45.154 --> 41:48.157
your breakfast sandwich
one morning.

41:48.201 --> 41:50.856
<i>You got a-a bagel egg sandwich.</i>

41:50.899 --> 41:53.685
And I said it was Jay
that took it, but it was me.

41:53.728 --> 41:55.034
What a bitch.

41:55.077 --> 41:56.731
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

41:56.775 --> 41:58.864
Your Birkin bag is still here.

41:58.907 --> 42:01.170
<i>I can't believe you just left
this here during COVID.</i>

42:01.214 --> 42:02.998
I had to leave in a rush.

42:03.042 --> 42:04.260
<i>Well, do you want me
to just put it in</i>

42:04.304 --> 42:05.610
<i>with all the other stuff?</i>

42:05.653 --> 42:07.786
No. You keep it.

42:07.829 --> 42:09.004
<i>What? No.</i>

42:09.048 --> 42:10.353
Yeah.

42:11.354 --> 42:12.878
<i>Okay.</i>

42:12.921 --> 42:14.314
<i>-I'm keeping it.</i>

42:14.357 --> 42:15.837
<i>Because of the bagel.</i>

42:15.881 --> 42:17.143
-Think of me when you use it. <i>
-No.</i>

42:17.186 --> 42:21.669
You think of me when I use it.

42:23.671 --> 42:26.021
God, I'm gonna miss you guys.

42:28.328 --> 42:31.113
I'm gonna miss this.

42:32.854 --> 42:35.988
You make me smile.

42:36.031 --> 42:39.644
I didn't smile much
before you guys.

42:39.687 --> 42:43.212
I smiled all the time,
but I didn't mean it.

42:43.256 --> 42:45.214
So then this is goodbye?

42:46.868 --> 42:49.828
I think I'm crying, so probably.

42:50.916 --> 42:53.832
I have to go.
This is getting too emotional.

42:57.923 --> 42:59.054
Goodbye.

42:59.098 --> 43:00.839
Goodbye, Lucca.

43:00.882 --> 43:03.015
You were one of the best.

43:03.058 --> 43:04.886
No.

43:06.192 --> 43:08.455
But together...

43:08.498 --> 43:11.153
we really were.

43:44.447 --> 43:46.754
God, have you ever seen
anything like it?

43:46.798 --> 43:48.234
It's so...

43:48.277 --> 43:50.192
It's so fucked.

43:50.236 --> 43:51.846
But there's a good side.

43:51.890 --> 43:53.805
Trump's people bring,

43:53.848 --> 43:56.024
what, 63 cases
against the election?

43:56.068 --> 43:58.505
They lose 62.

43:58.548 --> 44:02.422
Seems to me the guardrails held
just fine.

44:02.465 --> 44:04.990
-System worked.
-Yay...

44:05.033 --> 44:06.731
Liz. Liz.

44:06.774 --> 44:09.342
Sometimes when things work out,

44:09.385 --> 44:11.083
there is no parade.

44:11.126 --> 44:14.564
There's no congratulations,
but I'll tell you this.

44:16.175 --> 44:17.959
We live to fight another day.

44:18.003 --> 44:20.483
Yeah? Then why are you leaving
the law?

44:20.527 --> 44:22.442
Hmm.

44:23.486 --> 44:25.358
I am moving to Atlanta.

44:27.142 --> 44:29.231
-I'm s-- What?
-What?

44:29.275 --> 44:31.930
I am moving to Atlanta.

44:31.973 --> 44:35.803
I-I read this op-ed
by a man named Charles Blow.

44:35.847 --> 44:39.285
He's talking about Black people
returning to the South

44:39.328 --> 44:44.377
to create and consolidate
real political power.

44:44.420 --> 44:46.858
Those wins in Georgia
inspired him.

44:46.901 --> 44:47.989
-Mm.
-And I'll tell you.

44:48.033 --> 44:50.383
Inspired me, too.

44:50.426 --> 44:52.037
-Have you ever lived there?
-No.

44:52.080 --> 44:55.954
But if today told us anything,
it's about starting over.

44:55.997 --> 44:58.086
I am starting over.

44:58.130 --> 45:00.088
Here's to you.

45:01.829 --> 45:03.178
What about you two?

45:03.222 --> 45:05.485
-Ooh...
-Well, we lost Lucca.

45:05.528 --> 45:08.227
We're losing you. I...

45:09.358 --> 45:13.449
But my guess is that
the-the Biden administration

45:13.493 --> 45:15.364
is gonna be better
for Black businesses,

45:15.408 --> 45:17.410
-so...
Mm-hmm.

45:17.453 --> 45:18.977
Will you replace me?

45:19.020 --> 45:22.241
I think the big question is,
are you replacing me?

45:24.199 --> 45:26.027
Well, I...

45:26.071 --> 45:27.812
It's not my intention.

45:27.855 --> 45:30.031
No.

45:30.075 --> 45:32.077
Well, I can't change
the color of my skin.

45:32.120 --> 45:33.513
I know.

45:33.556 --> 45:36.037
Hey, I'm gonna fight
for my partnership.

45:38.039 --> 45:39.475
I know.

45:40.868 --> 45:42.000
I will leave it there, ladies.

45:43.566 --> 45:45.612
Aw.

45:45.655 --> 45:47.222
Bye, boss.

45:47.266 --> 45:49.529
We're all gonna miss you.

45:49.572 --> 45:51.444
-Come on.

45:52.619 --> 45:54.186
-Mmm...

46:07.547 --> 46:09.375
You sure you know
what you're doing?

46:09.418 --> 46:11.333
No.

46:11.377 --> 46:14.902
But I'm all about improvisation,
right?

46:17.165 --> 46:19.864
-What about you two?
Well, it...

46:19.907 --> 46:21.953
I-It's going to be interesting.

46:21.996 --> 46:23.302
Yes.

46:28.002 --> 46:30.048
Diane is a terrific lawyer,

46:30.091 --> 46:32.137
but this firm belongs to you.

46:32.180 --> 46:33.878
Your dad built it.

46:33.921 --> 46:36.054
Uh, n-- He did, Liz.

46:36.097 --> 46:38.404
Despite all his faults.

46:38.447 --> 46:41.581
You got to run this place
the way you want.

46:41.624 --> 46:45.063
This is a Black firm.

46:45.106 --> 46:47.935
And after today...

46:47.979 --> 46:51.983
the world needs Black firms.

46:52.026 --> 46:53.636
You got me?

46:56.030 --> 46:57.945
I got it.

47:12.655 --> 47:14.440
I'll see you.

47:36.027 --> 47:37.985
-Hey!
-Hey.
-What's up? What's up?

47:38.029 --> 47:38.986
-Hey.
-What you guys doing here?

47:39.030 --> 47:39.987
Packing for Lucca.

47:40.031 --> 47:41.162
It's weird.

47:41.206 --> 47:42.642
Everybody fun is leaving.

47:42.685 --> 47:44.470
-Hey! Hi. Hello.

47:44.513 --> 47:47.038
-Okay, everybody except for us.
-Okay.

47:47.081 --> 47:49.127
-How you doing?
-Uh...

47:49.170 --> 47:51.477
Well, I think I'm what they call
a long-hauler.

47:51.520 --> 47:53.479
-But I'm feeling good.
Oh!

47:53.522 --> 47:55.133
Oh, oh, oh! God!
Wait, wait, wait.

47:55.176 --> 47:56.438
H-Have you guys heard?

47:56.482 --> 47:58.571
-What?
-Well, uh, Trump...

47:58.614 --> 48:01.617
Trump pardoned
all of the convicted

48:01.661 --> 48:04.359
and corrupt Republican
officials.

48:04.403 --> 48:06.492
Makes sense.

48:06.535 --> 48:09.277
And Julius got a pardon, too.

48:09.321 --> 48:10.670
-What?
-Yes.

48:10.713 --> 48:12.367
-Julius?
-Julius.

48:12.411 --> 48:14.761
-You're kidding?
-Oh, my God!

